  "id": "predictions-zarr",
  "title": "FTW Global — Field Prediction Probabilities (Zarr)",
  "description": "Per-pixel class probabilities from the [PRUE model](https://huggingface.co/wherobots/prue-pt2), run over the FTW global Sentinel-2 feature mosaics, as a single cloud-native **Zarr V3** datacube. Three softmax bands — `non_field_background`, `field`, `field_boundaries` — at ~10 m (`8.983119e-5°`) on a global EPSG:4326 grid, for two prediction years (2024 and 2025). The cube has dimensions `(time, band, y, x)` = `(2, 3, 1566049, 4007517)`, float32. It shares the exact grid of the `features/zarr` mosaic, so features and predictions are directly stackable (open both with `xarray`/`rasterix`). The field-boundary `vectors` collection and the `confidence` raster are derived from these probabilities.\n\nThis is a GeoZarr-style store (CF-1.8, with the emerging Zarr `proj:`/`spatial:` geo-conventions) but **does not yet implement multiscales/overviews, so it is not yet web-viewable** — that work is in progress. For now it is best consumed analytically (xarray/Zarr), not as map tiles.",
  "license": "CC-BY-4.0",
